main event: A UFO was reported over Osgood, Indiana, on March 25, 1961, displaying a bright light and disappearing intermittently.
interesting points: The UFO was observed moving from south to north at high speed for approximately 15 minutes., The object had a bright light in the center and appeared bluish-green., Coordination with the National Space Surveillance Center confirmed tracking of an object over Osgood at the same time as the sighting., Witnesses believed the object was not an airplane, satellite, meteor, or star., The object increased speed suddenly and disappeared from sight.
witness description: The witness reported a bright light that changed visibility intermittently and was not identifiable as a conventional aircraft or celestial object.
